# Cursor IDE Rules for AccNext Project

## SQL Keywords Highlighting
SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, CREATE, DROP, ALTER, TABLE, DATABASE, INDEX, FROM, WHERE, JOIN, INNER, LEFT, RIGHT, OUTER, ON, GROUP, ORDER, BY, HAVING, LIMIT, OFFSET, AS, DISTINCT, COUNT, SUM, AVG, MAX, MIN, NULL, NOT, AND, OR, LIKE, IN, BETWEEN, EXISTS, UNION, CASE, WHEN, THEN, ELSE, END

## JavaScript/TypeScript Keywords Highlighting
const, let, var, function, async, await, Promise, import, export, default, class, interface, type, enum, namespace, module, extends, implements, public, private, protected, static, readonly, abstract, super, this, new, typeof, instanceof, void, undefined, null, true, false, if, else, switch, case, default, for, while, do, break, continue, return, try, catch, finally, throw, with

## Thai Language Support
- Use UTF-8 encoding for all files
- Support Thai language in comments and strings
- Follow Thai naming conventions for user-facing elements

## Code Style Guidelines
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Follow ESLint and Prettier configurations
- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Use PascalCase for components and classes
- Use kebab-case for file names
- Add JSDoc comments for functions and classes
- Use meaningful variable names in English for code, Thai for user interface

## Database Naming Conventions
- Use snake_case for table and column names
- Prefix tables with appropriate namespace
- Use singular nouns for table names
- Add created_at and updated_at timestamps to all tables